## Enforcement Model

Silver Bullet's quality enforcement happens through three layers in Forge:

1. **Skills (auto-applied)** — at `~/forge/skills/` and `.forge/skills/`. Forge picks the right skill based on context. ~106 skills loaded — silver-feature, silver-bugfix, silver-ui, silver-devops, silver-release, silver-spec, silver-quality-gates, silver-blast-radius, all 9 review-* skills, all Anthropic engineering/design/product-management/marketing skills, Superpowers skills, etc.

2. **Hook-equivalent agents (you invoke as tools)** — at `~/forge/agents/` and `.forge/agents/`. These replace the automatic firing of SB hooks on Claude Desktop. You **must** invoke them as tools at the gating moments listed below.

3. **GSD subagents (you invoke as tools)** — at `~/forge/agents/`. These replace `Task(subagent_type=…)` from Claude Code with proper Forge custom-agent delegation. ~31 GSD subagents available.

---

## Mandatory Hook-Agent Invocations

These agents must be invoked as tools at specific moments. Skipping them is treated as a workflow violation.

| Moment | Invoke | Behavior |
|---|---|---|
| Before `git commit` (intermediate) | `forge-pre-commit-audit` | Verifies `required_planning` skills (default: `silver-quality-gates`) before allowing commit |
| Before `gh pr create`, `gh release create`, production deploy | `forge-pre-pr-audit` | Verifies the full `required_deploy` skill list before allowing PR/release/deploy |
| Before declaring task complete or stopping work | `forge-task-complete-check` | Same gate as above, applied at session-end |
| Before commit when staging a phase `SUMMARY.md` | `forge-roadmap-freshness` | Confirms ROADMAP.md checkbox is ticked |
| Before any production build (`npm run build`, `vite build`, `cargo build --release`, etc.) | `forge-spec-floor-check` | Confirms `.planning/SPEC.md` exists and is substantive |
| Before `gh pr create` for UAT-eligible phases | `forge-uat-gate` | Confirms UAT.md exists with PASSED status |
| When creating a PR | `forge-pr-traceability` | Confirms PR description references REQ-IDs and phase number |
| After `git push`, before next commit | `forge-ci-status-check` | Confirms CI is green on the branch |
| Before applying any SB/GSD skill | `forge-forbidden-skill-check` | Confirms the skill is not deprecated |

Each agent returns either `ALLOW: <reason>` or `BLOCK: <reason>`. On `BLOCK`, **do not proceed** until the user fixes the underlying condition.

