## Iron Rules

### TDD (when implementing logic)
**No production code without a failing test first.** Write RED test, watch it fail for the right reason, write minimal GREEN, all tests pass. Apply the `test-driven-development` skill for the full cycle.

### Quality Gates
Before any non-trivial production code commit, apply `silver-quality-gates` (or `devops-quality-gates` for IaC). All 9 dimensions must pass — a single ❌ is a hard stop.

### Plugin Boundary
Never modify `~/forge/skills/` or `~/forge/agents/` from inside a project session. Treat them as read-only build artifacts. Project-specific overrides go in `.forge/skills/` and `.forge/agents/`.

### Trivial Bypass
For typo/config/docs-only changes (≤3 files), the session is "trivial" and gating agents return ALLOW automatically. The first non-trivial source-code edit removes the trivial marker and arms the gates.

### Backlog Capture
When `silver-quality-gates` flags a deferred item, immediately apply `silver-add` to file it as a backlog issue. Don't silently drop suggestions.

